The paper investigates the reliability of SSD-based I/O caching architectures used in enterprise storage systems, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also explores the impact of workload dependent parameters on the reliability of I/O cache, which can be considered as a statistical analysis (cs.ST). The paper implements an I/O cache scheme using an open-source I/O cache module in Linux operating system, which falls under the category of Architecture (cs.AR) and Operating Systems (cs.OS). Finally, the paper investigates the impact of power outage and high temperature faults on the reliability of I/O cache, which can be considered as a system-level analysis (cs.SY).
